This paper focuses on the design of conversational agents and understanding what people value in conversation. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the challenges in designing conversational agents, which falls under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also touches on the importance of context and relationship stage, which could be related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SD) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
